bottler
Homonym Number:  1
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:someone or something that is considered outstanding, excellent; something superior, splendid, excellent of its kind; corker, beaut; (or ironically) for soething or someone eccentrically out of the ordinary, dag


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: 1951 14 M 14 St Bede's, Chch 4 BOTTLER [someone/something liked] ;1960 17C M B6 St Bede's, Chch 8 BOTTLER [something good]
